  "body": "# ðŸ“‹  Milestone/Epic Tracker ![GitHub issues by-label](https://img.shields.io/github/issues/chainsafe/lodestar/scope-lightclients)\r\nThis tracker is to monitor issues and PRs relating to light clients for Lodestar. This issue deprecates #2986. \r\nLodestar's Light Client Demo: https://github.com/ChainSafe/eth2-light-client-demo\r\n\r\n\r\n### ðŸŸ¥  High Priority\r\n- [x] https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/issues/3952\r\n\r\n### ðŸŸ§  Medium Priority\r\n- [ ] https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/issues/2985\r\n- [x] https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/issues/3079\r\n- [ ] https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/issues/3077\r\n- [ ] https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/issues/3618\r\n\r\n### ðŸŸ¨  Low Priority\r\n\r\n\r\n## External Light Client References\r\n- https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/pull/2802\r\n   - **For implementation**\r\n- https://github.com/ethereum/beacon-APIs/pull/181\r\n- https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/pull/2267\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Medium-Long Term Planning\r\n\r\n### 1. Consensus Layer \r\n- Light client server: Allows head sync, but is censorable.\r\n- Improve approaches to minimizing censorship (Multiple end servers, P2P layers (Portal Network?)\r\n- Incentives Research (How do we find a way to prove real usage to compensate and incentivize running light client servers?)\r\nMinimize censorable (End servers instead of one. Less censorable, P2P layer like portal?)\r\nIncentives?? Find a way to prove real usage of a network with\r\n\r\n### 2. Networking Layer\r\n- Browsers not p2p friendly\r\n\r\n### 3. Userland \r\n- Get useful data - L1 data (e.g. balances)\r\n  - Query account balance + ERC20 balance: Pre-requisite https://github.com/ethereumjs/ethereumjs-monorepo/pull/1590\r\n\r\n### 4. Layer 2 Light Clients\r\n\r\n\r\n",
